description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Patient Environment Assistant – Cardiology 3 South/4 North West&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Band &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;2 £18,005 - £19,337&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An excellent opportunity has arisen to join the team in Cardiology at Royal Papworth Hospital. We are looking for motivated and dynamic team members who would be interested in becoming a &lt;strong&gt;Patient Environment Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; (PEA).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiology is a fast paced busy area with a high turnover of patients where PEAs are required and are vital in supporting the rest of the team in achieving the smooth running of the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job includes a daily/weekly/monthly cleaning and maintenance of equipment in both Cardiology Wards and maintaining areas like corridor, clean utility, equipment room, dirty utility, sluice and store rooms, responsible for doing daily water flushing and liaising with teams like procurement as well as completing tasks set by the ward managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PEAs are responsible in assisting in cleaning areas between patient moves and following the infection control standard required for the patient group. Organise and manage their workload with guidance from the nurse in charge and keeping up to date and accurate records of all the unit cleaning activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for a job where you will job a fantastic, supportive team where standards of care and environmental safety always come first, where there is an instant satisfaction and reward for completed tasks, where every day is different and filled with challenges, this is the role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential criteria for this post:&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; • Good communicator and approachable personality.&lt;br /&gt; • Ability to work within a large team of nurses, doctors and other professionals.&lt;br /&gt; • Caring, reliable, honest, hardworking and a good team player.&lt;br /&gt; • Ability to work in a busy, fast moving and physically demanding environment.&lt;br /&gt; • Ability to cope with competing priorities.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Experience in an acute healthcare setting is desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To find out more an informal visit is highly recommended&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charge Nurse Steven Thurston or Sister Rebecca Thomas on 01223 638306.&lt;/p&gt;
